summary: An ordinance appropriating the sum of Four Hundred Dollars ($400.00)out of the general fund of the City of Seattle, to pay claim of Edward Watson and L. Ethel Watson, for personal injuries received by the said L. Ethel Watson, on the 21st day of June, 1917, on the sidewalk upon the northeast side of Pike Place in the City of Seattle opposite the Market between Stewart and Virginia Streets; and authorizing the drawing of a warrant therefor.
